<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4951884>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURE 2. Pherusa affinis (Leidy, 1855), paraneotypes (USNM 1251742). A. Anterior end, dorsal view. B. Same, ventral view. C. Non-type specimen (USNM 40214), anterior end, oblique dorsal view. D. Same, head, frontal view (branchiae and palps removed; BS: branchial scar, LL: lateral lip, PS: palp scar). E. Another paraneotype (USNM1251742), chaetiger 10, right notopodium (insets: basal and medial chaetal regions). F. Same, chaetiger 21, right neuropodium (insets: neurochaetal tips). Scale bars: A: 0.80 mm, B: 0.76 mm, C: 1.2 mm, D: 0.70 mm, E: 110 µm, F: 100 µm." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4951884/files/figure.png" .

